				<div itemprop="commentText" class='post entry-content '>
					<!--cached-Mon, 14 Jul 2014 08:17:57 +0000-->Sorry, I probably should&#39;ve mentioned this in my initial post. My colleagues (and myself) _are_ doctors, and we&#39;re all a bit baffled by the phenomenon. I&#39;m the only musician of the group though, so I haven&#39;t got anyone to compare with when it comes to &quot;wear and tear&quot;. One of my colleagues mentioned that she has seen plenty of runners coming into her office complaining of knees and ankles snapping at every step, and she simply puts it down to wear and tear, and says it&#39;s harmless. Neither her nor me have ever heard of *small* joints (i.e. fingers) snapping this much though.
					
